    <item>
      <title>Accesibble Frugality: Barcelona Trastos Map and Data</title>
      <link>https://jruizcabrejos.com/post/accessible-frugality-barcelona-trash-collection-data-20250201/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 01 Feb 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://jruizcabrejos.com/post/accessible-frugality-barcelona-trash-collection-data-20250201/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;proverb&#34;&gt;Proverb&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;One man&amp;rsquo;s trash is another man&amp;rsquo;s treasure&amp;rdquo; is a &lt;del&gt;proverb&lt;/del&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://wordlust.blogspot.com/2006/10/pithicism.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;pithicism&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;page-note-anchor&#34;&gt;
    &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-ref&#34; id=&#34;page-note-ref-8&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-8&#34; aria-label=&#34;See note 8&#34;&gt;
      &lt;sup&gt;8&lt;/sup&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;span class=&#34;page-note&#34; id=&#34;page-note-8&#34; role=&#34;note&#34;&gt;
      &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-number&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-ref-8&#34; aria-label=&#34;Back to reference 8&#34;&gt;8&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;span class=&#34;page-note-content&#34;&gt;Play on words from a &amp;rsquo;euphemism-collector&#39;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt; that I have, over time, grown to be fond of.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the city of Barcelona, Catalonia, there is a good chance you will find something interesting in between the junk and laid waste. Every day people transiting the streets tend to partake on this activity (picking up &amp;ldquo;trash&amp;rdquo;) for a few reasons.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;./figure1_me.png&#34; alt=&#34;Me on the garbage&#34; style=&#34;width: 60%; height: auto;&#34;&gt;
&lt;figcaption&gt;Figure 1. The beer was not found in the trash. Taken in Paris, France, 2022.&lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Some do it out of necessity, or desperation, as is the case of the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ecologiapolitica.info/recicladores-informales-barcelona/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;more than ~3,000&lt;/a&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;lsquo;trash scavengers&amp;rsquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;page-note-anchor&#34;&gt;
    &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-ref&#34; id=&#34;page-note-ref-9&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-9&#34; aria-label=&#34;See note 9&#34;&gt;
      &lt;sup&gt;9&lt;/sup&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;span class=&#34;page-note&#34; id=&#34;page-note-9&#34; role=&#34;note&#34;&gt;
      &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-number&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-ref-9&#34; aria-label=&#34;Back to reference 9&#34;&gt;9&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;span class=&#34;page-note-content&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;English&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt; roaming among containers for pieces of metal and other scraps to make a living out of recycling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is for many a profession, often informal, and nowadays predominantly associated with immigrants, despite the trade having &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LbjgCCcCOl4&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;a long history within locals&lt;/a&gt; going back &lt;a href=&#34;https://eltranvia48.blogspot.com/2015/03/los-traperos-en-la-historia-de-barcelona.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;centuries&lt;/a&gt;, with some &lt;em&gt;&amp;lsquo;drapaires&amp;rsquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;page-note-anchor&#34;&gt;
    &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-ref&#34; id=&#34;page-note-ref-10&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-10&#34; aria-label=&#34;See note 10&#34;&gt;
      &lt;sup&gt;10&lt;/sup&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;span class=&#34;page-note&#34; id=&#34;page-note-10&#34; role=&#34;note&#34;&gt;
      &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-number&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-ref-10&#34; aria-label=&#34;Back to reference 10&#34;&gt;10&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;span class=&#34;page-note-content&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Catalan&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt; having achieved &lt;a href=&#34;https://catalunyaplural.cat/ca/cal-drapaire-o-la-genesis-duna-llegenda/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;long-lasting cultural legacies&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And, because nothing is sacred under capitalism, it is also a business worth almost 10,000 million euros, in which recycling is estimated to move &lt;a href=&#34;https://distintaslatitudes.net/indispensables-pero-invisibles/migrantes-chatarreros-en-barcelona&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;1% of the country GDP every year&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Chances are, you have also seen or met your local &lt;em&gt;&amp;lsquo;chatarrero&amp;rsquo;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;page-note-anchor&#34;&gt;
    &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-ref&#34; id=&#34;page-note-ref-11&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-11&#34; aria-label=&#34;See note 11&#34;&gt;
      &lt;sup&gt;11&lt;/sup&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;span class=&#34;page-note&#34; id=&#34;page-note-11&#34; role=&#34;note&#34;&gt;
      &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-number&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-ref-11&#34; aria-label=&#34;Back to reference 11&#34;&gt;11&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;span class=&#34;page-note-content&#34;&gt;&lt;em&gt;Spanish&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt; at one time or another.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;./figure2_chatarrero_google_search.png&#34; alt=&#34;Chatarrero picture google&#34;&gt;
&lt;figcaption&gt;Figure 2. &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Other individuals pick up trash in a more recreational manner, almost as if it were a sport, or some form of &lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20090520052742/http://www.basurama.org/safaribasura.htm&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;safari&lt;/a&gt; in which you are hunting for furniture that could be salvaged or restored.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Among privileged immigrants, furnishing your new apartment with something found on the streets tends to be an experience shared by many&lt;span class=&#34;page-note-anchor&#34;&gt;
    &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-ref&#34; id=&#34;page-note-ref-12&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-12&#34; aria-label=&#34;See note 12&#34;&gt;
      &lt;sup&gt;12&lt;/sup&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;span class=&#34;page-note&#34; id=&#34;page-note-12&#34; role=&#34;note&#34;&gt;
      &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-number&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-ref-12&#34; aria-label=&#34;Back to reference 12&#34;&gt;12&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;span class=&#34;page-note-content&#34;&gt;I wanted to call it an &amp;lsquo;almost universal experience&amp;rsquo;, but I digress, I need data to prove that&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt; in social media.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;./figure3_instareels.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Instagram Reels with the average immigrant experience&#34;&gt;
&lt;figcaption&gt;Figure 3. &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Similar to thrifting clothes, sometimes all it takes is one really good find.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;beggars-cant-be-choosers&#34;&gt;Beggars can&amp;rsquo;t be choosers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Where and when can I salvage old, abandoned, furniture in Barcelona?&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a question that my friends, friends of friends, coworkers and myself have asked from time to time (as unlikely as it may sound).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, the town hall (Ajuntament/Municipality) of Barcelona only provides this information for individual street searches.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;./figure4_barcelona_trastos_UI.png&#34; alt=&#34;UI of the website&#34; style=&#34;width: 60%; height: auto;&#34;&gt;
&lt;figcaption&gt;Figure 4. &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This makes it &lt;del&gt;impossible&lt;/del&gt; annoyingly difficult to have a simple map with exact locations and dates in order to plan for any trash rummaging expedition.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And although some maps exist for specific districts, a single image containing all of the information for the whole of Barcelona remains elusive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;a-picture-is-worth-a-thousand-words&#34;&gt;A picture is worth a thousand words&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In 2010 Zara Patterson was the first to make a &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.google.com/maps/d/u/0/viewer?mid=1l2VAhplHwkWYhNi6WOcDeqnxPoE&amp;amp;shorturl=1&amp;amp;ll=41.396674791413474%2C2.1627183782959447&amp;amp;z=13&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;public online map&lt;/a&gt; with information regarding when, and where, one could throw (or in this case, find) old furniture in the streets of Barcelona.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;She did so as part of her blog &lt;a href=&#34;https://caerengracia.wordpress.com/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Caer en Gracia&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt; where she &lt;a href=&#34;https://caerengracia.wordpress.com/eco-recursos/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;lists resources to carry on restoration and renovation works ecologically&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;./map_caerengracia.png&#34; alt=&#34;Old Map&#34;&gt;
&lt;figcaption&gt;Figure 5. &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, the map has a few inaccuracies, with certain neighborhoods within districts not displaying the right pick up day of the week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The map was last updated in 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A second map, of low resolution and similarly outdated, sometimes also &lt;a href=&#34;https://vaciadosbarcelona.com/dia-de-recogida-de-muebles-en-barcelona/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;makes the rounds within the internet&lt;/a&gt;. It was originally from a 2011 article that is no longer accessible &lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20110626070437/http://www.bcn.es/publicacions/b_informacio/bi_91/08-09.pdf&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;unless you use the Wayback Machine&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;./map_pixelated_2011.png&#34; alt=&#34;Old Map&#34;&gt;
&lt;figcaption&gt;Figure 6 &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;there-is-more-than-one-way-to-skin-a-cat&#34;&gt;There is more than one way to skin a cat&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since I couldn&amp;rsquo;t find a complete, up-to-date map of Barcelona with the days of the week in which furniture/trastos are collected, I compiled the data from the Ajuntament website and made my own maps.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I did this in two steps:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;First, I downloaded a dataset containing all of the street names within the city of Barcelona from the portal &lt;a href=&#34;https://opendata-ajuntament.barcelona.cat/data/es/dataset/carrerer&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Open Data Barcelona&amp;rdquo;&lt;/a&gt;. With this information, I then set up a data scrapper with RSelenium. This scrapper looped through all the streets available in the website.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;./firefox_hYxHdfeUpx.gif&#34; alt=&#34;Animation of data scrapping&#34; style=&#34;width: 60%; height: auto;&#34;&gt;
&lt;figcaption&gt;Figure 7 &lt;/figcaption&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Then, once all the data for each street/number is collected, I geocoded&lt;span class=&#34;page-note-anchor&#34;&gt;
    &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-ref&#34; id=&#34;page-note-ref-13&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-13&#34; aria-label=&#34;See note 13&#34;&gt;
      &lt;sup&gt;13&lt;/sup&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;span class=&#34;page-note&#34; id=&#34;page-note-13&#34; role=&#34;note&#34;&gt;
      &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-number&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-ref-13&#34; aria-label=&#34;Back to reference 13&#34;&gt;13&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;span class=&#34;page-note-content&#34;&gt;gave them a latitude/longitude coordinate&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt; each street name with the OpenStreet Map API, using the httr2 package.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This two-step procedure is &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/jruizcabrejos/barcelona_trastos_eng&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;documented in the github for this project&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;it-is-what-it-is&#34;&gt;It is what it is&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And if you are reading this, these maps are now yours too, and I hope you find something nice in the trash.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src=&#34;./eng_Map_Barcelona_Furniture_Junk_Map_days.png&#34; alt=&#34;barcelona_map_trastos&#34;&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;pithicism&#34;&gt;Pithicism&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It took me more than a year to finish writing this blog post properly. The scrapping script went through several iterations until I had something that worked &amp;ldquo;cleanly&amp;rdquo; enough&lt;span class=&#34;page-note-anchor&#34;&gt;
    &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-ref&#34; id=&#34;page-note-ref-14&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-14&#34; aria-label=&#34;See note 14&#34;&gt;
      &lt;sup&gt;14&lt;/sup&gt;
    &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;span class=&#34;page-note&#34; id=&#34;page-note-14&#34; role=&#34;note&#34;&gt;
      &lt;a class=&#34;page-note-number&#34; href=&#34;#page-note-ref-14&#34; aria-label=&#34;Back to reference 14&#34;&gt;14&lt;/a&gt;
      &lt;span class=&#34;page-note-content&#34;&gt;or that I liked enough&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As of April 5, 2026, I can call this done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Did you know, read, or heard about &lt;em&gt;frugality&lt;/em&gt; before?&lt;/p&gt;


    
